+# Pi05 With OpenVINO
+
+## Environment Setup
+
+### By UV
+
+Ensure you have `uv` installed. You can set up the environment and install dependencies by running:
+
+```bash
+uv sync --extra pi-ov
+```
+Note: Running inference on GPU requires `openvino>=2026.0`.
+
+Then run python file by:
+
+```bash
+uv run --extra pi-ov <your_python_file>
+```
+Using `--extra pi-ov` will force the use of the CPU version of PyTorch.
+
+## Convert Pi05 model to OpenVINO
+
+### Convert Model without RTC (Original)
+
+Use the `convert_ov.py` script to convert the standard Pi05 model to OpenVINO IR. This process typically goes through ONNX export.
+
+
+Example:
+```bash
+uv run --extra pi-ov scripts/convert_ov.py \
+    --torch_dir <path_to_pytorch_checkpoint> \
+    --ov_output_dir pi05_lerobot_ov_ir \
+    --onnx_output_dir pi05_onnx \
+    --override
+```
+If `--compress_int8`, `nncf` is required.
+```bash
+uv run --extra pi-ov --with nncf scripts/convert_ov.py \
+    --torch_dir <path_to_pytorch_checkpoint> \
+    --ov_output_dir pi05_lerobot_ov_ir \
+    --onnx_output_dir pi05_onnx \
+    --compress_int8 \
+    --override
+```
+Use a sample from a local LeRobotDataset to generate representative inputs during the export/conversion process:
+```bash
+uv run --extra pi-ov --with nncf scripts/convert_ov.py \
+    --torch_dir <path_to_pytorch_checkpoint> \
+    --dataset_path <path_to_local_dataset> \
+    --ov_output_dir pi05_lerobot_ov_ir \
+    --onnx_output_dir pi05_onnx \
+    --compress_int8 \
+    --override
+```
+
+**Arguments:**
+- `--torch_dir`: Path to the pretrained PyTorch model checkpoint or huggingface repo. Default: "lerobot/pi05_base"
+- `--ov_output_dir`: Directory where the OpenVINO IR model will be saved.
+- `--onnx_output_dir`: Directory where the intermediate ONNX model will be saved.
+- `--dataset_path`: (Optional) Path to a local LeRobotDataset directory. If provided, the converter uses dataset stats and the first sample to build real preprocessed inputs (instead of random dummy inputs) for ONNX export.
+- `--compress_int8`: (Optional) Compress weights to INT8. `nncf` is required.
+- `--save_fp32`: (Optional) Save OpenVINO model in FP32 format (FP16 by default).
+- `--override`: (Optional) Overwrite existing files.
+- `--camera_num`, `-c`: (Optional) Number of cameras (batch size for image input). Default: 4.
+
+
+### Convert Model with RTC
+
+Use the `convert_ov_rtc.py` script to convert the Pi05 model with Real-Time Chunking (RTC) logic embedded. 
+
+Example:
+```bash
+uv run --extra pi-ov --with nncf scripts/convert_ov_rtc.py \
+    --torch_dir <path_to_pytorch_checkpoint> \
+    --dataset_path <path_to_local_dataset> \
+    --onnx_output_dir pi05_rtc_onnx \
+    --ov_output_dir pi05_rtc_lerobot_ov_ir \
+    --compress_int8 \
+    --override
+```
+Arguments are the same as above.
+
+## Test Pi05 Policy
+Run script to test policy (In the project directory):
+```bash
+uv run --extra pi-ov tests/policies/pi0_pi05/test_pi05_ov.py \
+    --model_dir <ov_model_dir> \
+    --device CPU \
+    -n 10
+```
+
+**Arguments:**
+- `--model_dir`: Directory containing the OpenVINO model (xml and bin files).
+- `--device`: Target device for inference (e.g., "CPU", "GPU"). Default: "CPU".
+- `-n`, `--num_runs`: Number of inference runs to average for benchmarking. Default: 10.
+- `--run_torch`: (Optional) Run the original PyTorch model instead of OpenVINO for comparison.
+
diff --git a/examples/pi05_with_openvino/scripts/convert_ov.py b/examples/pi05_with_openvino/scripts/convert_ov.py
new file mode 100644
